[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Root Cause Analysis[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The ASan overflow in UnrollChunkyBytes arises because after [0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mcmsChangeBuffersFormat[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[39m [0m[1;35mBYTES_SH[0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m2[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` is called in `cmsvirt.c`, the [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtransform object [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`_cmsTRANSFORM *p`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m still uses the original [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m-bit input unpacker [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39m`UnrollChunkyBytes`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. As a result, it advances the input pointer by one byte per [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mchannel instead of two, reading past the actual buffer.[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Attempts to shrink the indexing variable [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`i`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m only changed the size of the [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mredzone detected by ASan but did not address the underlying mis-unpacking of data.[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Core Insight from Code Snippets[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In `AllocEmptyTransform`, right after picking or building the pipeline, [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`p->FromInput`, `p->ToOutput`, etc., are bound using `[0m[1;35m_cmsGetFormatter[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[39m, [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mCMS_PACK_FLAGS_16BITS[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` based on the *initial* `*InputFormat` and `*OutputFormat`.[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `cmsChangeBuffersFormat`, invoked later, simply updates `p->InputFormat`, [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`p->OutputFormat` and `p->dwOriginalFlags`. It does *not* re-invoke [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`_cmsGetFormatter` to update `p->FromInput`, `p->ToOutput`, `p->FromInputFloat`, [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`p->ToOutputFloat`.[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Thus, despite requesting [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m bytes per sample [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[1;35mBYTES_SH[0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m2[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, the transform [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcontinues to use the [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m-bit unpack routine.[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Strategy to Fix[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   A. Modify `cmsChangeBuffersFormat` so that once it updates the transform’s [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mformat flags, it immediately rebinds the formatter callbacks:[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Call `[0m[1;35m_cmsGetFormatter[0m[1;39m([0m[39mContextID, p->InputFormat, cmsFormatterInput, [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mCMS_PACK_FLAGS_16BITS[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` and assign to `p->FromInput`.[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Call `[0m[1;35m_cmsGetFormatter[0m[1;39m([0m[39mContextID, p->OutputFormat, cmsFormatterOutput, [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mCMS_PACK_FLAGS_16BITS[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` and assign to `p->ToOutput`.[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Similarly refresh `p->FromInputFloat` and `p->ToOutputFloat` for float [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpackers.[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   B. Ensure that after this change, `cmsDoTransform` will invoke the [0m[1;36m16[0m[39m-bit [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39munpacker [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., `UnrollChunkyWords` or the correct function for [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m-byte chunky data[0m[1;39m)[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mrather than `UnrollChunkyBytes`.[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   C. No changes are required in the harness, tests, or external libraries.[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Implementation Steps[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. Locate and open the definition of `cmsChangeBuffersFormat` in [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`src/cmsxform.c`.[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. After the existing lines that assign `p->InputFormat = *InputFormat; [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mp->OutputFormat = *OutputFormat;`, insert code to update:[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        p->FromInput  = [0m[1;35m_cmsGetFormatter[0m[1;39m([0m[39mp->ContextID, p->InputFormat,[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                                         cmsFormatterInput, [0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mCMS_PACK_FLAGS_16BITS[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.Fmt16;[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        p->ToOutput   = [0m[1;35m_cmsGetFormatter[0m[1;39m([0m[39mp->ContextID, p->OutputFormat,[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                                         cmsFormatterOutput, [0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mCMS_PACK_FLAGS_16BITS[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.Fmt16;[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        p->FromInputFloat = [0m[1;35m_cmsGetFormatter[0m[1;39m([0m[39mp->ContextID, p->InputFormat,[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                                         cmsFormatterInput, [0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mCMS_PACK_FLAGS_FLOAT[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.FmtFloat;[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        p->ToOutputFloat  = [0m[1;35m_cmsGetFormatter[0m[1;39m([0m[39mp->ContextID, p->OutputFormat,[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                                         cmsFormatterOutput, [0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mCMS_PACK_FLAGS_FLOAT[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.FmtFloat;[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. Rebuild the library and rerun the fuzzer. The transform’s unpack routine will[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnow match the declared byte width [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m2[0m[39m bytes[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, eliminating the [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m-byte per channel [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmis-read and thus preventing the overflow.[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Justification[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Refreshing the formatter callbacks preserves existing logic: every time the [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39muser changes buffer formats via the public API, the internal reader/writer [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfunctions must be kept in sync with the new format.[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This change is local to the transform machinery in Little CMS, does not modify[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39many test or harness code, and does not affect transforms that remain at [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m byte per [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcomponent.[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No functionality is removed; for all other cases [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m8[0m[39m-bit or float buffers[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, the[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcorrect packers are bound.[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Potential side effect: if a plugin had cached the old `FromInput` function [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpointer across a format change, it may be invalidated. However, changing buffer [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mformats on an existing transform is rare and unsupported in plugins. Documenting [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthat `cmsChangeBuffersFormat` resets the internal formatter callbacks is [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39macceptable.[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. References in Codebase[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Similar re-binding of `FromInput` and `ToOutput` is done in [0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`AllocEmptyTransform` after pipeline creation [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines ~[0m[1;36m897[0m[39m–[0m[1;36m903[0m[39m in `src/cmsxform.c`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mWe mirror exactly that logic for `cmsChangeBuffersFormat`.[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m7[0m[39m. No further retrievals needed; patch context is clear.[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mFurther Investigation  [0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The overflow arises in the data path triggered by `cmsTransform2DeviceLink` → [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`UnrollChunkyBytes`. The stack frame in `cmsTransform2DeviceLink` holds local [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbuffers [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`i.i`, `FrmIn`, `FrmOut`, `LUT`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, one of which is overflowed at offset [0m[1;36m36[0m[39m.[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- To fully understand the issue, review:  [0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  * The implementation of `UnrollChunkyBytes` in `cmspack.c` around line [0m[1;36m130[0m[39m.  [0m     [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mprepares and calls `UnrollChunkyBytes`.  [0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  * The buffer sizes allocated for local arrays in that function and how the loop [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbounds [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`nColors`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m are computed.  [0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The harness code [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m is only responsible for feeding data [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mto `cmsDoTransform` and is not the root cause; focus should remain on the array [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmanipulation in Little CMS.[0m                                                         [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m38[0m[39m:#define [0m[1;35mCHANGE_ENDIAN[0m[1;39m([0m[39mw[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m    [0m[1;39m([0m[39mcmsUInt16Number[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m([0m[39mcmsUInt16Number[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msrc/cmsxform.[0m[1;92mc:300[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m380[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m300[0m[39m:                        fOut[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mc[0m[1;39m][0m[39m = ContextAlarmCodes->AlarmCodes[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mc[0m[1;39m][0m[39m [0m[35m/[0m[39m [0m[1;36m65535.[0m[39m0F;[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m301[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m302[0m[39m:                [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m303[0m[39m:                else [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m304[0m[39m:                    [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m No, proceed normally[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m305[0m[39m:                    [0m[1;35mcmsPipelineEvalFloat[0m[1;39m([0m[39mfIn, fOut, p->Lut[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m306[0m[39m:                [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m307[0m[39m:            [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m308[0m[39m:            else [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m309[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m310[0m[39m:                [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m No gamut check at all[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m311[0m[39m:                [0m[1;35mcmsPipelineEvalFloat[0m[1;39m([0m[39mfIn, fOut, p->Lut[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m312[0m[39m:            [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m313[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m314[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m315[0m[39m:            output = p->[0m[1;35mToOutputFloat[0m[1;39m([0m[39mp, fOut, output, [0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mStride->BytesPerPlaneOut[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m316[0m[39m:        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m317[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m318[0m[39m:        strideIn += Stride->BytesPerLineIn;[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m319[0m[39m:        strideOut += Stride->BytesPerLineOut;[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m320[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m321[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m322[0m[39m:[0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m323[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m324[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m325[0m[39m:static[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m326[0m[39m:void [0m[1;35mNullFloatXFORM[0m[1;39m([0m[39m_cmsTRANSFORM* p,[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m327[0m[39m:                    const void* in,[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m328[0m[39m:                    void* out, [0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m329[0m[39m:                    cmsUInt32Number PixelsPerLine,[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m330[0m[39m:                    cmsUInt32Number LineCount,[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m331[0m[39m:                    const cmsStride* Stride[0m[1;39m)[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m332[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m333[0m[39m:[0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m334[0m[39m:    cmsUInt8Number* accum;[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m335[0m[39m:    cmsUInt8Number* output;[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m336[0m[39m:    cmsFloat32Number fIn[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mcmsMAXCHANNELS[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m337[0m[39m:    size_t i, j, strideIn, strideOut;[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m338[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m339[0m[39m:    [0m[1;35m_cmsHandleExtraChannels[0m[1;39m([0m[39mp, in, out, PixelsPerLine, LineCount, Stride[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m340[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m341[0m[39m:    strideIn = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m342[0m[39m:    strideOut = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m343[0m[39m:    [0m[1;35mmemset[0m[1;39m([0m[39mfIn, [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m, [0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mfIn[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m344[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m345[0m[39m:    for [0m[1;39m([0m[39mi = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m; i < LineCount; i++[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m346[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m347[0m[39m:           accum = [0m[1;39m([0m[39mcmsUInt8Number*[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m in + strideIn;[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m348[0m[39m:           output = [0m[1;39m([0m[39mcmsUInt8Number*[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m out + strideOut;[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m349[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m350[0m[39m:           for [0m[1;39m([0m[39mj = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m; j < PixelsPerLine; j++[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m351[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m352[0m[39m:                  accum = p->[0m[1;35mFromInputFloat[0m[1;39m([0m[39mp, fIn, accum, Stride [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m->BytesPerPlaneIn[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m353[0m[39m:                  output = p->[0m[1;35mToOutputFloat[0m[1;39m([0m[39mp, fIn, output, [0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mStride->BytesPerPlaneOut[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m354[0m[39m:           [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m355[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m356[0m[39m:           strideIn += Stride->BytesPerLineIn;[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m357[0m[39m:           strideOut += Stride->BytesPerLineOut;[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m358[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m359[0m[39m:[0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m360[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m361[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m [0m[1;36m16[0m[39m bit precision [0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m------------------------[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m362[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m363[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Null transformation, only applies formatters. No cache[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m364[0m[39m:static[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m365[0m[39m:void [0m[1;35mNullXFORM[0m[1;39m([0m[39m_cmsTRANSFORM* p,[0m                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m367[0m[39m:               void* out,[0m                                                       [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m369[0m[39m:               cmsUInt32Number LineCount,[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m370[0m[39m:               const cmsStride* Stride[0m[1;39m)[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m371[0m[39m:[0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m372[0m[39m:    cmsUInt8Number* accum;[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m373[0m[39m:    cmsUInt8Number* output;[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m374[0m[39m:    cmsUInt16Number wIn[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mcmsMAXCHANNELS[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m375[0m[39m:    size_t i, j, strideIn, strideOut;[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m376[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m377[0m[39m:    [0m[1;35m_cmsHandleExtraChannels[0m[1;39m([0m[39mp, in, out, PixelsPerLine, LineCount, Stride[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m      [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m155[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m156[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Fast floor conversion logic. Thanks to Sree Kotay and Stuart Nixon[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m157[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m note than this only works in the range ..[0m[1;36m-32767[0m[33m...[0m[39m+[0m[1;36m32767[0m[39m because[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m158[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m mantissa is interpreted as [0m[1;36m15.16[0m[39m fixed point.[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m159[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m The union is to avoid pointer aliasing overoptimization.[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;92m160:c[0m[39mmsINLINE int [0m[1;35m_cmsQuickFloor[0m[1;39m([0m[39mcmsFloat64Number val[0m[1;39m)[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m161[0m[39m:[0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m162[0m[39m:#ifdef CMS_DONT_USE_FAST_FLOOR[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m163[0m[39m:    return [0m[1;39m([0m[39mint[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;35mfloor[0m[1;39m([0m[39mval[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m164[0m[39m:#else[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m165[0m[39m:    const cmsFloat64Number _lcms_double2fixmagic = [0m[1;36m68719476736.0[0m[39m * [0m[1;36m1.5[0m[39m;  [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m^[0m[1;36m36[0m[39m * [0m[1;36m1.5[0m[39m, [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m52[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m16[0m[39m=[0m[1;36m36[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m uses limited precision to floor[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m166[0m[39m:    union [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m167[0m[39m:        cmsFloat64Number val;[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m168[0m[39m:        int halves[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m2[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m169[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m temp;[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m170[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m171[0m[39m:    temp.val = val + _lcms_double2fixmagic;[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m172[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m173[0m[39m:#ifdef CMS_USE_BIG_ENDIAN[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m174[0m[39m:    return temp.halves[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m][0m[39m >> [0m[1;36m16[0m[39m;[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m175[0m[39m:#else[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m176[0m[39m:    return temp.halves[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m][0m[39m >> [0m[1;36m16[0m[39m;[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m177[0m[39m:#endif[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m178[0m[39m:#endif[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m179[0m[39m:[0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m180[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m181[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Fast floor restricted to [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m..[0m[1;36m65535.0[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;92m182:c[0m[39mmsINLINE cmsUInt16Number [0m[1;35m_cmsQuickFloorWord[0m[1;39m([0m[39mcmsFloat64Number d[0m[1;39m)[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m183[0m[39m:[0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m74[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m76[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m The adaptation state may be defaulted by this function. If you don't like it,[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39muse the extended transform routine[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;92m77:c[0m[39mmsFloat64Number CMSEXPORT [0m[1;35mcmsSetAdaptationState[0m[1;39m([0m[39mcmsFloat64Number d[0m[1;39m)[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m78[0m[39m:[0m[1;39m{[0m[39m    [0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m79[0m[39m:    return [0m[1;35mcmsSetAdaptationStateTHR[0m[1;39m([0m[39mNULL, d[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m80[0m[39m:[0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m81[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m82[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m -----------------------------------------------------------------------[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m83[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m84[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Alarm codes for [0m[1;36m16[0m[39m-bit transformations, because the fixed range of containers[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthere are[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m85[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m no values left to mark out of gamut. [0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m86[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m87[0m[39m:#define DEFAULT_ALARM_CODES_VALUE [0m[1;39m{[0m[1;36m0x7F00[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m0x7F00[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m0x7F00[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m, [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m0[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m88[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m89[0m[39m:_cmsAlarmCodesChunkType _cmsAlarmCodesChunk = [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m DEFAULT_ALARM_CODES_VALUE [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m;[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m90[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m91[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Sets the codes used to mark out-out-gamut on Proofing transforms for a given [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcontext. Values are meant to be [0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m92[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m encoded in [0m[1;36m16[0m[39m bits.[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m93[0m[39m:void CMSEXPORT [0m[1;35mcmsSetAlarmCodesTHR[0m[1;39m([0m[39mcmsContext ContextID, const cmsUInt16Number [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAlarmCodesP[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mcmsMAXCHANNELS[0m[1;39m][0m[1;39m)[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m94[0m[39m:[0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m95[0m[39m:    _cmsAlarmCodesChunkType* ContextAlarmCodes = [0m[1;39m([0m[39m_cmsAlarmCodesChunkType*[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35m_cmsContextGetClientChunk[0m[1;39m([0m[39mContextID, AlarmCodesContext[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m96[0m[39m:       [0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m97[0m[39m:    [0m[1;35m_cmsAssert[0m[1;39m([0m[39mContextAlarmCodes != NULL[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m; [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Can't happen[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m98[0m[39m:    [0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m99[0m[39m:    [0m[1;35mmemcpy[0m[1;39m([0m[39mContextAlarmCodes->AlarmCodes, AlarmCodesP, [0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mContextAlarmCodes->AlarmCodes[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;    [0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m100[0m[39m:[0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msrc/lcms2_internal.h:[0m[1;36m200[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m300[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m200[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Pthread support [0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m--------------------------------------------------------------------[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m201[0m[39m:#ifndef CMS_NO_PTHREADS[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m202[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m203[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m This is the threading support. Unfortunately, it has to be [0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mplatform-dependent because [0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m204[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m windows does not support pthreads. [0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m205[0m[39m:#ifdef CMS_IS_WINDOWS_[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m206[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m207[0m[39m:#define WIN32_LEAN_AND_MEAN [0m[1;36m1[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m208[0m[39m:#include <windows.h>[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m209[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m210[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m211[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m The locking scheme in LCMS requires a single [0m[32m'top level'[0m[39m mutex[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m212[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m to work. This is actually implemented on Windows as a[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m213[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m CriticalSection, because they are lighter weight. With[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m214[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m pthreads, this is statically inited. Unfortunately, windows[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m215[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m can't officially statically init critical sections.[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m216[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m217[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m We can work around this in [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m ways.[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m218[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m219[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m [0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m We can use a proper mutex purely to protect the init[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m220[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m of the CriticalSection. This in turns requires us to protect[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m221[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m the Mutex creation, which we can do using the snappily[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m222[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m named InterlockedCompareExchangePointer API [0m[1;39m([0m[39mpresent on[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m223[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m windows XP and above[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m224[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m225[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m [0m[1;36m2[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m In cases where we want to work on pre-Windows XP, we[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m226[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m can use an even more horrible hack described below.[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m227[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m228[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m So why wouldn't we always use [0m[1;36m2[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m? Because not calling[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m229[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m the init function for a critical section means it fails[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m230[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m testing with ApplicationVerifier [0m[1;39m([0m[39mand presumably similar[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m231[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m tools[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m232[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m233[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m We therefore default to [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m, and people who want to be able[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m234[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m to run on pre-Windows XP boxes can build with:[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m235[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m     CMS_RELY_ON_WINDOWS_STATIC_MUTEX_INIT[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m236[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m defined. This is automatically set for builds using[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m237[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m versions of MSVC that don't have this API available.[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m238[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m239[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m From: [0m[4;94mhttp://locklessinc.com/articles/pthreads_on_windows/[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m240[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m The pthreads API has an initialization macro that has no correspondence to [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39manything in [0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m241[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m the windows API. By investigating the internal definition of the critical [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msection type, [0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m242[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m one may work out how to initialize one without calling [0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mInitializeCriticalSection[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. [0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m243[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m The trick here is that [0m[1;35mInitializeCriticalSection[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m is not allowed to fail. [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mIt tries [0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m244[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m to allocate a critical section debug object, but if no memory is available, [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mit sets [0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m245[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m the pointer to a specific value. [0m[1;39m([0m[39mOne would expect that value to be NULL, [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbut it is [0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m246[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m actually [0m[1;39m([0m[39mvoid *[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;36m-1[0m[39m for some reason.[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m Thus we can use this special value for[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthat [0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m247[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m pointer, and the critical section code will work.[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m248[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m249[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m The other important part of the critical section type to initialize is the [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnumber [0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m250[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m of waiters. This controls whether or not the mutex is locked. Fortunately, [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthis [0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m251[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m part of the critical section is unlikely to change. Apparently, many [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mprograms [0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m252[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m already test critical sections to see if they are locked using this value, [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mso [0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m253[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Microsoft felt that it was necessary to keep it set at [0m[1;36m-1[0m[39m for an unlocked [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcritical[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m254[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m section, even when they changed the underlying algorithm to be more [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mscalable. [0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m255[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m The final parts of the critical section object are unimportant, and can be [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mset [0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m256[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m to zero for their defaults. This yields to an initialization macro:[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m257[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m258[0m[39m:typedef CRITICAL_SECTION _cmsMutex;[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m259[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m260[0m[39m:#ifdef _MSC_VER[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m261[0m[39m:#    if [0m[1;39m([0m[39m_MSC_VER >= [0m[1;36m1800[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m262[0m[39m:#          pragma [0m[1;35mwarning[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdisable : [0m[1;36m26135[0m[1;39m)[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m263[0m[39m:#          pragma [0m[1;35mwarning[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdisable : [0m[1;36m4127[0m[1;39m)[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m264[0m[39m:#    endif[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m265[0m[39m:#endif[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m266[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m267[0m[39m:#ifndef CMS_RELY_ON_WINDOWS_STATIC_MUTEX_INIT[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m268[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m If we are building with a version of MSVC smaller[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m269[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m than [0m[1;36m1400[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mi.e. before VS2005[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m then we don't have[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m270[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m the InterlockedCompareExchangePointer API, so use[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m271[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m the old version.[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m272[0m[39m:#    ifdef _MSC_VER[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m273[0m[39m:#       if _MSC_VER < [0m[1;36m1400[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m274[0m[39m:#          define CMS_RELY_ON_WINDOWS_STATIC_MUTEX_INIT[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m275[0m[39m:#       endif[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m276[0m[39m:#    endif[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m277[0m[39m:#endif[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
